        <h1>Mesarthim</h1>
        <p style="align: center;">(2003)</p>
        <table class="table">
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Remote Mining Town<br>
                <br>
                The focus of this environment was to experiment with modular construction, while trying to match the graphical standards for a PC RPG at that time. This project took 2 weeks.<br>
                <br>
                This was one of the first implementations for real-time 3D I created individually that involved both visual content creation and scripting.<br>
                <br>
                Polycount: 29,612 not including particle systems<br>
                Texture memory: 18MB<br>
                Models authored in 3dsMax 5.1<br>
                Textures authored in Photoshop 7 with combination of hand painting and photogrammetry.<br>
                <br>
                This has a playable demo here:<br>
                &nbsp;</td>
